  <discussion>Tortula amplexa is similar to T. inermis but the latter is autoicous and lacks the leaf border.  The lax areolation, sheathing perichaetial leaves, and weak development of the laminal papillae distinguish it from the similar T. bolanderi.  This species is thought to spread by rhizoidal propagula through inadvertent human agency (A. G. Side and H. L. K. Whitehouse 1974).</discussion>
